Putting Calender events 
------------------------

1. Kick Off Meeting - meet & Greet , Intro to Bikex Club & Scrum
2. Sprint Planning 
3. Sprint Daily Scrum 
4. Sprint Review 
5. Sprint Refinement 
10. Sprint Retrospective 


Key Points 

- A ne sprint starts immediately after the conclusion of previous sprint 
- Sprints are designed ensure inspection and adaption of progress towards a product Goal
- at least every calendar month 
- Sprint Goal is single objective for the sprint 
- When the sprint horizon is too long, the sprint Goal may become invalid 
- Complexity may rise risk may be increased 
- Shorter sprints for more learning cycles and limit risk of cost and effort to a smaller time frame
- sprint may be considered a short project 
